FBIS4-7018 "dreas080_c_94009" FBIS-EAS-94-080 Daily Report 22 Apr 1994 North Korea Hanchongnyon Vows To Confront ROK Government Hanchongnyon Vows To Confront ROK Government SK2204103894 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1014 GMT 22 Apr 94 SK2204103894 Pyongyang KCNA English BFN [Text] Pyongyang, April 22 (KCNA) -- Kim Hyon-chun, chairman of the South Korean Federation of General Student Councils (Hanchongnyon), at a recent press conference expressed the resolve of his federation to win in its confrontation with the pro-U.S. traitorous "government," a South Korean newspaper reported. Noting that "Hanchongnyon at its congress of second-term representatives early this month branded the Kim Yong-sam regime as a pro-U.S. traitorous regime," Kim Hyon-chun said: "We will unite all people including the one million students under the slogan of independence, democracy and reunification and lay a foothold for victory in our confrontation with the Kim Yong-sam regime."
